      "date": "2015-11-12 15:37:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIt would be better to define\n\n \nstruct lu_rdbuf {\n        unsigned int rb_nbufs;\n        struct lu_buf rb_bufs[];\n};\n\nThen you can skip allocating each rb_bufs[i] individually and there is no need for the tti_rdbuf member of struct tgt_thread_info.\n\nNote that rb_bytes is set but never read.\n\nAlso I think that tgt_send_buffer() should take a struct l_wait_info * parameter so that we do not have this problem again.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b85a9efa55d5fced885a229c0d6a4c819c42cb2a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
